text.section:
The governing boards of each institution may elect to purchase interest in real property, contractual services, rentals of all types, supplies, materials, equipment, printing, and services, except that competitive bids may not be required for:
Contractual services where no competition exists;
Food, clothing, equipment, supplies, or other materials to be used in laboratory and experimental studies;
Instructional materials available from only one (1) source;
Where rates are fixed by law or ordinance;
Library books;
Commercial items that are purchased for resale;
Professional, technical, scientific, or artistic services, but contracts shall be submitted in accordance with KRS 45A.690 to 45A.725;
All other commodities, equipment, and services which, in the reasonable discretion of the board, are available from only one (1) source; and
Interests in real property.
